    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-02-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-02-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="338"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d338">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">756D.5–MAP/2–2851</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-02-28">February 28,
                            1951</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have today allocated to the
                    Department of Defense the sum of $2,000,000 from funds made available by the
                    Second Supplemental Appropriation Act, 1950<note n="1" xml:id="d338fn1">Approved
                        July 26, 1950; 64 Stat. 373.</note> to carry out the provisions of section
                        303(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) of the Mutual Defense Assistance Act of
                        1949,<note n="2" xml:id="d338fn2">Approved October 28, 1949; 63 Stat.
                        973.</note> as amended.</p>
                <p>The allocated funds are to be utilized for programs of military assistance to
                    Indonesia. These programs are to be prepared in general conformity with your
                    letter of February 8, 1951 to the Director of the Bureau of the Budget.<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d338fn3">Frederick J. Lawton. In this letter of February 8,
                        from Secretary of State Acheson to Mr. Lawton, which is not here printed,
                        Mr. Acheson asked that the remaining $2,000,000 of an original $5,000,000
                        budgeted for equipping the Indonesian constabulary be allocated immediately
                        to the Department of Defense to continue the program
                        (756D.5–MAP/2–851).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Truman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
